Linux basic
----------------------------------------------------
sudo service --status-all
sudo service --status-all | grep <service_name>
sudo service <service_name> status
ps -ef
ps -ef | grep <service_name>
systemctl status <service_name>
ps aux
ps aux | grep <postgres>

short keys
1. Shift+F5 : reflesh the page ignoring the cache


journalctl -u service-name.service
Following option
-b see only log messages for the current boot
--no-pager will print full log
-e will start the log at the end
-f will follow (print) updates to the log
--help will let you see all available options
